{title: Bouquet In Heaven}
{artist: J.D. Crowe}
{composer: Written by Lester Flatt}

[3/4 time]
[C]When it's [F]decoration day up in [C]Heaven
There's a bouquet I'm longing to [G7]see
There's a [C]flower some[C7]where in this [F]bouquet
That [C]means all the [G7]world to [C]me
Now tonight the old home place is [F]lonely
Since [C]mother has been called [G7]away
